mods.abstract: The California Magazine of Western Square and Round Dancing by the Square Dancers of Southern California. This edition includes a table of contents which lists the following: SQUARE DANCES "After They've Seen Paree", "K. O.", and "The Philanderer". ROUND DANCES "Dreaming", and "Happy Polka". SPECIAL FEATURES "Square Dance Records - 1956", "Records for Rounds", "A Chance to Help", "A Training Course for the Caller's Wife", "Square Dancing in Wiesbaden", "Music and Sound, Part II", "Saint Louis Synopsis", "Oakland, Nebraska, Swings In", "St. Louis Come-On", and ""This is Your Record - Johnny Schultz". REGULAR FEATURES "From the Floor", "As I See It", "Style Series: Grand Square", "The Square Dance Picture", "Square of the Month (Bruce Stotts)", "'Round the Outside Ring", and "Calendar of Square Dancing Events".
